the first 10' of the street-side yard.

visual_elements.description: Figure 33: Examples of site planning solutions for attached garages/carports. The diagram shows three different lot configurations (two interior lots and one corner lot) with various garage and parking arrangements. Each lot includes a 'Buildable area', 'Main dwelling', and 'Parking structure' (attached garage). The diagrams illustrate front yards, rear yards, interior-side yards, and for the corner lot, a street-side yard. Uncovered parking spaces are also shown. A key defines various line types and shaded areas.
visual_elements.location: Middle to bottom of the page

visual_elements.description:
A legend for the diagram, defining graphical elements:
- Solid thick line: Curb
- Solid thin line: Lot line
- Hatched grey area: Sidewalk
- Dashed line: Required setbacks
- Dashed outline with light grey fill: Buildable area
- Dark grey fill: Dwelling
- Black fill: Parking structure
- Hatched white area: No-parking area
- Car icon with light grey fill: Uncovered space
